 This invention relates to accumulator mechanisms for use in computing machines, and more particularly accumulators of the creep carry type. 
 The advantages 0! creep accumulators with differential gearing over snap carry accumulators is well known in the computing machine art. The 
 features which are valuable to any computing mechanism. I 
 Accumulators using diiierential gears and the creep means of carrying may be divided into two One of these classes includes the spur gear arrangement where the carry ratio is obtained by a similar ratio of gear teeth. An example 0! this class may be found in U. S. Patent No. 2,214,029'issued to H. P. Mixer, September 10, 1940, or in U. 8. Patent No; 2,211,736, issued to H. T. Avery, August 13, 1940. The second class- The present invention is applicable to both oi these classes. 
 Generally stated, the invention has for its principal object to facilitate the visual reading oi totals and the taking of totals by clearing the accumulator, in accumulatqs of the creep carry ype. 
One of the objects of the present invention isto rectify the creep increments in a series or reading dials o! a creep carry accumulator whereby the correct accumulated amount may be read after each addition. 
 The above mentioned patent, 1,828,180, is a good example of the prior art computing machines which make use of a creep-crawl accumulator having an internal floating gear. The construction permits a total to be indicated only when the orders are zeroized one after another, starting from the lowest or .units order, The present invention has for one of its oblects to provide a construction which permits the orders to be zeroized simultaneously regardless of the accumulator position. 
 A creep carry accumulator can be cleared by engaging it with its actuating racks and advancability to run in either direction at high speed and into cooperation therewith, provided each and every one or said wheels stands either in its zero position or advanced addltively not more than nine spaces. fractional amount greater than 9 and iess than 10 that the trouble occurs, and especially when that amount is nearly 10; There is a critical zone in the fractional positions of a resultant wheel. between the 9 and 0 positions, where there is at least the danger that the stop would an, in front of the stop lug and arrest the wheel immediately, which has made it necessary to restore the wheels of a creep carry accumulator successively. To bridge this zone is an object of the invention. This is done by providing a latching mechanism for the zero stops which automatically holdsthe which will be any described herein and particularly pointed out in the claims. I 
 The prior art machines that rectify the cree crawl accumulator wheels do so by subtracting the creep out of the wheel movements by turning them in a reverse direction. The present invention starts a computing operation by subtracting a unit from the indicator in each denominational order; then, when the amount isto be read or printed, the creep is rectified by adding to each indicator, an amount equal to one-tenth oi the I ten complement of the amount in the next lower Fig. 3 taken from the left and shows most of thein: said racks simultaneously in subtracting direction each until it is arrested by a stop lug on the resultant wheel engaging a zero stop brought order accumulator wheel. 
